@NODE Install "Installation"
@{B}Installation@{UB}
Just unpack the archive to anywhere you want it.
Then run TView and a settings window should pop up.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"
Run TView and watch the magic.
If everything goes well , the settings window should open if you
don't have a TView.config file. Choose your settings and channels here.
Then go to menu/tools/"Get Data" to fetch the channels you have chosen.

When everything is configured, this is what you "should" do :)
Have the Start.rexx installed so the fetching of data is automatic.
Then use the search to find your favourite programs. Save settings again.
Now mark the programs which you want to see with Alarm. Iconify TView.
Wait until the nice requester appears and go watch TV.
It should be possible to config InfraJoy/InfraBox/AirLink to change
channel on TV to the channel the program is running on also. When I have
the chance to try, I will!

 @{" Show      " Link Show} - The show cycle gadget.
 @{" Time      " Link Time} - The time slider.
 @{" List      " Link List} - The program listing.
 @{" Info      " Link Info} - The more info listing.
 --- Menu ----
 @{" Get Data  " Link GetData} - Download the programs.
 @{" Show all  " Link ShowAll} - List all programs
 @{" Search    " Link Search} - Search for something specific.
 @{" Alarm     " Link Alarm} - Don't wanna miss something?
 @{" Arexx     " Link Arexx} - The commands.
 @{" Save/Load " Link SaveLoad} - Nice feature

 @{" Settings " Link Settings} - Settings window.

 You can copy a list by standard amiga clipboard, right-amiga-A + C

@ENDNODE

